Mind-controlled Mouse
The three study participants are part of a clinical trial to test a brain-computer interface (BCI) called BrainGate. BrainGate translates participantâ€™s brain activity into commands that a computer can understand. In the new study, researchers first implanted microelectrode arrays into the area of the brain that governs hand movement. The participants trained the system by thinking about moving their hands, something the BCI learned to translate into actions on the screen.
